default4.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe recent NHS reforms provide a clear opportunity to address these poor practices and focus on improving outcomes for people affected by LUTS.
default 
defaultA key part of the new NHS quality improvement framework is the introduction of quality standards, prepared by the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE), which 
defaultdescribe markers of high quality care that, when delivered collectively, should improve the effectiveness, safety and experience of care for people with a particular condition.
default 
default&#xa0;
default4.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAstellas welcomes 
defaultNICE’s 
defaultplans to develop quality standards for LUTS in men and urinary incontinence in women 
defaultwhich will provide a set of concise statements designed to drive quality improvements across a pathway of care.
default 
defaultThese will provide useful tools for commissioners and providers when designing and monitoring performance of their local continence services.
default 
defaultTo succeed, we believe that the final set of statements and supporting metrics should focus on those approaches and interventions that will ultimately make the most difference in terms of patient outcomes, including increased symptom awareness, earlier identification of symptoms and timely access to the best possible quality treatment and supportive care.
default 
default&#xa0;
default4.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs part of its expanded remit, 
defaultNICE
default now also has
default responsibility for developing 
defaultguidance and 
defaultquality standards 
defaultin
default social care. 
defaultEncouragingly, 
defaultNICE is considering
default developing a social care quality standard on promoting continence and preventing and managing incontinence in adults in care homes and the community.
default 
defaultIt is important that any supporting statements and metrics for social care are closely aligned with those included in health quality standards to ensure consistency in the provision of care across both settings.
default 
